phaser 3.90.0 how to kill tweens
In Phaser 3.90.0, the most efficient ways to "kill" or stop tweens are to target specific objects, use the Tween Manager, or call methods directly on a tween instance.
1. Kill All Tweens for a Specific Object 
If you want to stop every tween currently affecting a specific Game Object (like a sprite), use killTweensOf. This is the cleanest way to ensure an object stops moving before you destroy it or start a new animation. 
Phaser Docs
Phaser Docs
 +1
javascript
// Stops and removes all tweens targeting 'mySprite'
this.tweens.killTweensOf(mySprite);

// You can also pass an array of targets
this.tweens.killTweensOf([enemy1, enemy2, enemy3]);
Use code with caution.

2. Kill a Specific Tween Instance
If you have a reference to a specific tween, you can stop it directly.
stop(): Immediately halts the tween. It flags the tween for removal by the Tween Manager, meaning it will be cleaned up in the next frame.
remove(): Immediately removes the tween from the manager's internal arrays and sets its state to REMOVED.
destroy(): Completely clears out the tween data and resets targets. A destroyed tween cannot be reused or played again. 
