Use code with caution.

3. Global Tween Management
To clear multiple tweens at once through the TweenManager: 
this.tweens.killAll(): Stops and removes every active tween in the current scene.
this.tweens.pauseAll() / this.tweens.resumeAll(): Use these if you only need to temporary halt movement without "killing" the tweens entirely. 
Quick Comparison of Methods
Method 	Effect	Best Use Case
killTweensOf(target)	Stops all tweens for a specific object.	Before destroying a sprite or changing its state.
tween.stop()	Halts a specific tween; flags for cleanup.	Standard way to end a single animation early.
tween.destroy()	Immediate data wipe of the tween.	When you are certain the tween is no longer needed.
tweens.killAll()	Stops every tween in the scene.	Resetting a level or switching game states.
Note: By default, Phaser tweens automatically destroy themselves once they finish playing unless you have set persist: true in the tween configuration. 
