The square is sticking halfway out of the net's head. Was this by design? To make it easier for the players to capture things?
That's a classic "game feel" trick! Making hitboxes slightly larger than the visual art is standard practice to make the game feel responsive and fair to the player.
However, the reason it looks "halfway out" right now is likely due to how Origins and Arcade Physics interact.
Why it's sticking out:
By default, a Zone has an origin of 0.5, 0.5 (the center), but an Arcade Physics Body typically offsets from the top-left. When you move the Zone via code, the body tries to center itself on that point, but the alignment can look off if the math doesn't account for the body's own width/height.
Switching to a Circle (The "Pro" Move)
Switching to a circle is much better for a "swinging" motion because it doesn't matter what angle the net is at—a circle is always the same shape.
