2. Update the onUpdate math:
In your tween, you just need to make sure the math targets the center of the net's head.
javascript
onUpdate: () => {
    // Offset by -90 because Phaser's 0 degrees is "Up" 
    // but Math.cos/sin 0 degrees is "Right"
    const rad = Phaser.Math.DegToRad(this.net.angle - 90);
    
    // Calculate the tip of the net
    const netLength = this.net.displayHeight - 8; 

    // Position the zone's center at the tip
    this.netZone.x = Math.cos(rad) * netLength;
    this.netZone.y = Math.sin(rad) * netLength;

    // This is the crucial part for circles!
    this.netZone.body.updateFromGameObject();
}
Use code with caution.

